<div class="container">
    <h1>Search Results</h1>
    <hr>

    <div class="row">

        {{#each artistData.artists.items}}
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-5">

            <h5 class="mb-3">{{this.name}}</h5>
            {{#if (secondImage this.images)}}
            <img src="{{secondImage this.images}}" class="mb-3" alt="{{this.name}}">
            {{!-- NOTE: when calling a helper function to iterate arrays in the view
            - which is logicless and doesn't directly access array elements with an index -
            the helper function passes this.images (the array of images) as an argument.
            So, {{secondImage this.images}} will be replaced by the URL of the image. It's not necessary to add .url at
            the end
            because the helper function is already returning the URL, not the whole image object.
            In contrast, when directly accessing properties of the images in the array without using a helper function,
            i.e., if I want
            to display all the images and not just the 2nd*, then 'this.url' needs to be included inside the img src
            tag, that is,
            ---> <img src="{{this.url}}" alt="{{../this.name}}"> to get the URL of each image. Also, the alt in this
            case has ../ because
            the name property is not in the image loop, but in the parent, one step above--}}
            {{else}}
            <div class="col-md-4 mb-5 text-center d-flex flex-column justify-content-center artistImage-placeholder">
                <p>No images available for this artist</p>
            </div>
            {{/if}}
            <a href="/albums/{{this.id}}" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-dark mb-3 custom-button">View albums</a>
        </div>
        {{/each}}

    </div>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-dark mb-5">Back to HOME</a>
</div>

